.\" -------------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH BUGS
.\"
.IP \(bu 4
Only one WireGuard interface is served by a single daemon process.
Peers on secondary interfaces will not receive PeerJS-based
hole-punching.
.IP \(bu 4
IPv6 NAT traversal is not implemented.
.IP \(bu 4
There is no SIGHUP reload; the daemon must be restarted to pick up
changes to configuration files.
.IP \(bu 4
STUN results are not cached between poll cycles; each outbound OFFER
triggers a fresh STUN query.
.IP \(bu 4
Symmetric-NAT topologies are mathematically unsupported by the
hole-punching model used here; no workaround exists within this
design.
.\"
